{% extends "base.njk" %}
{% block bodyclass %}
    home
{% endblock bodyclass %}
{% block content %}
    <section id="home-entry">
        {# <h1> #}
        {#     MetaR<span>OR</span> #}
        {# </h1> #}
        <img class="homeReuseLogo" src="/assets/images/logo-metaror.png" alt="">
        <h2>A new plaform for metaresearch</h2>
        <a href="/about">About MetaROR</a>
    </section>
    <section id="home-part2">
        <h2>Seamless Integration of Research and Review</h2>
        <p>
            At MetaROR, we empower researchers to enhance their work through an open and dynamic review process. Our platform
            supports the publication, review, and curation of academic preprints, ensuring transparency and rigour.
        </p>
        <ul id="home-publish-review-curate" class="pub-rev-cur">
            <li>
                <img src="/assets/images/img-publish.jpg"
                     alt="a person with a pen, ready to write on paper">
                <h3>Publish</h3>
                <p>
                    This initial step involves the researcher submitting their preprint to a preprint repository where it can be
                    accessed by peers and the public. This step is crucial for early dissemination and can facilitate broader
                    feedback and collaboration.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <img src="/assets/images/img-review.jpg"
                     alt="a type writer with writter Review on the paper">
                <h3>Review</h3>
                <p>
                    During this phase, reviewers can provide feedback, critiques, and suggestions. This peer review is conducted
                    openly, with reviews being visible to the public and becoming a part of the knowledge creation process.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <img src="/assets/images/img-curate.jpg"
                     alt="a person with a pen, ready to write on paper">
                <h3>Curate</h3>
                <p>
                    Editors assess the reviews and the preprint, providing an editorial assessment to contextualise the feedback and
                    quality of the work. This step adds a layer of validation to the research, so that high standards are
                    maintained.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="home-part3">
        <h2>Seamless Integration of Research and Review</h2>
        <p class="subtitle">MetaROR simplifies the path from preprint to publication with a clear, straightforward process</p>
        <div class="detailswrap">
            <details open>
                <summary>
                    <h3>Deposit your preprint</h3>
                </summary>
                <p>
                    You can deposit your preprint on the server of your choice, respecting your personal preferences or disciplinary
                    practices.
                </p>
                <p>MetaROR will work with all servers.</p>
            </details>
            <img src="/assets/images/deposit.jpg" alt="">
            <details>
                <summary>
                    <h3>Register your submission in MetaROR</h3>
                </summary>
                <p>
                    Once you have deposited your preprint, take note of its DOI or url and come to MetaROR, where you can register
                    your submission for open peer review.
                </p>
            </details>
            <img src="/assets/images/register.jpg" alt="">
            <details>
                <summary>
                    <h3>Get your work reviewed and curated</h3>
                </summary>
                <p>
                    As the reviews come in, they will be shared with you and be attached to your submission once they are moderated
                    by our editorial team. Once all reviews are in, our team will prepare an editorial assessment of your work.
                </p>
            </details>
            <img src="/assets/images/getyourwork.jpg" alt="">
            <details>
                <summary>
                    <h3>Submit your response</h3>
                </summary>
                <p>
                    Engage with reviewers’ and editorial feedback directly. Publish your responses and decide if you wish to revise
                    and resubmit your preprint.
                </p>
            </details>
            <img src="/assets/images/submit.jpg" alt="">
        </div>
    </section>
    <section id="home-part4">
        <ul>
            <li>
                <figure>
                    <img src="/assets/images/yourcurated.jpg" alt="">
                    <figcaption>
                        <h3>Your curated preprint can be the final product</h3>
                        <p>
                            For many researchers, a positive open review is sufficient to finalise their findings. At MetaROR, you can
                            choose to consider your work complete upon receiving favourable evaluations.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            If reviewers and editors have reservations, it's also up to you to decide whether a new version of the work
                            is necessary, and you can even publish a response and defend your original views instead.
                        </p>
                    </figcaption>
                </figure>
            </li>
            <li>
                <figure>
                    <img src="/assets/images/furtheropportunities.jpg" alt="">
                    <figcaption>
                        <h3>Further opportunities: Journal publishing</h3>
                        <p>
                            If you aim to publish in traditional journals, MetaROR supports you as well. Our reviews can accompany your
                            submissions, and we collaborate with several journals to streamline the submission process with
                            pre-validated research.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            If reviewers and editors have reservations, it's also up to you to decide whether a new version of the work
                            is necessary, and you can even publish a response and defend your original views instead.
                        </p>
                    </figcaption>
                </figure>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>
